About Project:

Project Name: Stopwatch Using C Language.
Author: Yogeshwar Prakash Chaudhari.
File Name: config.c

  A simple console-based stopwatch program written in C language, allowing users to start, stop, resume, and reset a timer using a menu-driven interface. 
This project demonstrates the use of loops, keyboard input handling, and time control in C.

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//
// Implemented Features:
//
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

- Start Stopwatch – Begin counting from 00:00:00  
- Stop Stopwatch – Pause the timer at the current time  
- Resume Stopwatch – Continue counting from where you stopped  
- Reset Stopwatch – Reset the timer to zero  
- Exit Program – Close the application gracefully  
- Non-blocking key input using `_kbhit()` and `_getch()`  
- Real-time delay control using `sleep()` function  

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//
// How It Works:
//
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

The stopwatch runs in real-time using a loop that increments the seconds value every second.  
Minutes and hours are updated automatically when seconds or minutes reach 60.  

Keyboard input is handled using:
- `_kbhit()`  Checks if a key is pressed (non-blocking)
- `_getch()`  Captures the pressed key

When the stopwatch is running, pressing 2 stops it and returns to the menu.
